Arch Linux Install

(These are personal notes for a basic install of Arch Linux. I made several attempts to
install for an UEFI set up while following the ArchWiki and could not get it right. 
I ended up watching this video from DT/Distrotube https://youtu.be/PQgyW10xD8s and it 
helped me understand it better so here

I am starting after the partition segment. I did premade partitions with gparted
from a live usb prior to this.


	--After creating partitions the way you want.

	$ pacstrap /mnt base linux linux-firmware
	$ genfstab -U /mnt >> /mnt/etc/fstab
	$ arch-chroot /mnt
	$ ln-sf /usr/share/zoneinfo/America/Chicago /etc/local/time
		if you need to find your city
		$ ls /user/share/info
	$ hwclock --systohc
	$ vim /locale.gen -uncomment your locale
	$ locale.gen
	$ vim /etc/hostname -add your hostname (pick any name)
	$ vim /etc/hosts
		- add
		-127.0.0.1	localhost
		-::1		localhost
		-127.0.0.1	primal.localdomain	primal
		-(primal was the hostname that i chose for my system)

	$ passwd
	$ useradd -m username
	$ passed username

	add member to groups
	$ usermod -aG wheel,audio,video,optical,storage
	$ pacman -S sudo
	$ EDITOR=vim visudo
		- go into file and uncomment line where you see wheelgroup

	$ pacman -S grub efibootmgr dosfstools os-prober mtools
	$ mkdir /boot/EFI
	$ mount /dev/sda2 /boot/EFI
	$ grub-install --target=x86_64-efi bootloader-id=grub_uefi --recheck
	$ grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg
	$ pacman -S networkmanager git
	$ systemctl enable NetworkManager
		-creates sym link
	$ exit
	$ reboot
